Abstract = {With the continuous increase of data, scaling up to unprecedented
   amounts, generated by Internet-based systems, Big Data has emerged as a
   new research field, coined as ``Big Data Science{''}. The core of Big
   Data Science is the extraction of knowledge from data as a basis for
   intelligent services and decision making systems, however, it
   encompasses many research topics and investigates a variety of
   techniques and theories from different fields, including data mining and
   machine learning, information retrieval, analytics, and indexing
   services, massive processing and high performance computing. Altogether
   the aim is the development of advanced data-aware knowledge based
   systems.
   This special issue presents advances in Semantics, Intelligent
   Processing and Services for Big Data and their applications to a variety
   of domains including mobile computing, smart cities, forensics and
   medicine. (C) 2014 Published by Elsevier B.V.},
